//Loop
While loop 

let a=10;
while(a>=0){
document.write(a);
a=a-1;
}

Do while loop will execute at second time. But in first time it will directly loop will execute.

do{
document.write(a);
a+=1;
}
while(a<=10);


//For loop
for(let a=10; a<10;a++){
document.write(a);
}

//Continue 
Will skip the particular iteration.

//Break
Will break the iteration in conditional statements.


const Arr= [2,5,7,8];
arr.push(6) - push or add the element at the end index of an array.

arr.pop() - remove the element at the end index of an array.

arr.unshift(9) --> add the element at the start index of an array.

arr.shift()--> remove the element of an array from the start index.

arr.reverse() -- reverse the array in lexical order.
arr.sort() -- sort the array in lexical order.

arr.sort(a,b)=>a-b  ==> in ascending order.

Merge 2 array 
Let b= [12,34,21];
arr.concat(b);
let c= arr+b;


