Query selector::

Query selector will work only for first tag / matched element.

Query selector All==>
But query SelectorAll will work on every match element. It will create a nodelist matches element.

Event Listener ==> 
When we are dealing the event trigger scenario for that purpose we are using it.
Like click, hover , keypress, mouse over and many more.

let x= document.querySelector("h1);
x.style.backgroundColor=red;
x.style.color=red;


setTimeOut( ()=>{
x.style.backgroundColor=red;
x.style.color=red;
},2000
);



x.addEventListner("click", ()=>{
x.style.backgroundColor=red;
x.style.color=yellow;
},5000);


Mouse Enter ::> changes done after the mouseEnter
x.addEventListner("mouseenter", ()=>{
x.style.backgroundColor=red;
x.style.color=yellow;
},5000);

Mouse Leave::> revert back the changes done with the help of mouseLeave

x.addEventListner("mouseleave", function(){
x.style.backgroundColor=red;
x.style.color=yellow;
},5000);


Map is not iteratable with for of , for in loop.



